stretcher /ˈstrɛtʃə/

(stretchered,stretchers) 

1. N-COUNT A stretcher is a long piece of canvas with a pole along each side, which is used to carry an injured or sick person. 担架 

例： The two ambulance attendants quickly put Plover on a stretcher and got him into the ambulance. 这两名救护车的救护员迅速把普洛弗放在担架上并抬进了那辆救护车。 

2. V-T PASSIVE If someone is stretchered somewhere, they are carried there on a stretcher. 用担架抬 

例： I was close by as Lester was stretchered into the ambulance. 莱斯特被用担架送进那辆救护车时我在旁边。

